flavor:
Man made weapons designed to be wielded by worse monsters. Are you a man or a monster? Rovin', chillin', killin'.
The black pistol deals more damage than the gray one, effectively making every other shot deadlier.
Made entirely of plastic, these fantastic pistols are designed to be used akimbo style and to guard your life.
A sub machinegun designed by the late gunsmith Elias von Vrede. Is said to have turned the tide in the Third War for the Hellthrone.
Designed by Elias von Vrede, the M3 Termite is a sister project to his namesake gun. Its complex internal magazine, though covered by a small metal shroud, is vulnerable to dust and debris.

Crude laser machinegun based on the guts of spirit foam mining equipment. Made and used by the workers rebellion in the aftermath of the second robot war. Fires faster and more accurately the longer you rev the handle.

Made largely out of repurposed sheet metal, this .50 BMG rifle features a massive spring with a draw force of over 400 newtons. The magazine "kick-forward" is said to have been inspired by the way Dolphins jump along the ocean's surface.
Standard issue commando pistol marked "S9 Taxi Special".
Sporty gallop based burst pistol with a foldable stock for stability. The sound compensates for the lack of horse sounds, after horses were replaced by hoverboards during the third robot war.
A laser sub machinegun once dubbed "the switchblade of personal defense weaponry" by Folks Magazine.

Ease of use and reliability are the selling points here. The Deathstar PG was released to the public along side the Rektor during the Second Robot wars, and made for civilian use. Nicknamed "Piggybank" due to the shake maneuver needed to align the bullets thrown into the hatch.
A machine gun made by the Haukland Company. Said to do double damage against Ghosts, but this is largely believed to be hearsay.
Foldable SMG inspired by Japanese minimal housing. Falsely claims to fit in your pocket. Beware consumers.
Features a patented dual casing ejection system that enables its extreme rate of fire.

While its initial purpose was aesthetic, a way to mix and match the colors of different components, the Salamander eventually turned into a favorite among clandestine agencies for its unmatched stealth potential, being snuck into high security locations.
A polymer furnished sniper rifle named after a forest in the northern wetlands. The teal bakelite has been treated with an oil derived from Sugar Snakes for increased durabililty.
A hydraulics assisted breaching shotgun. Model number denotes maximum shell capacity.
A buck-actionâ„¢ ranching gun, often found in the rough and tumble reaches of the outer circle.
A revolutionary revolver design that can be quickly reloaded due to its detachable cylinder. This model is intended for use by police forces.
A breech loaded, single-shot, small game hunting rifle.
Semi-automatic foldable shotgun inspired by Japanese minimal housing. The box in which it comes has a chibi mascot claiming "Lock & Fold!" as the main tagline.
A favorite among Dusian Metro Cops for its high rate of fire and erratic spread pattern.

Not much is known about this laser weapon, hence the name, the only lead being the symbol on the side. They are quite rare due to all of them ever being found at the site of a huge explosion at a supposedly empty field in Sulfur that just left a few crates of these along with metal and robotic scrap parts. It does not seem to be made for human hands, but its size makes it a good backup piece.

Produced in a long line of battle rifles, per royal order of Queen Andrielle the Third. Her Majesty kept insisting that each iteration of the rifle still wasn't good enough for adoption in her Regal Corps, hence the high model number.
Issued to school principals during the second Robot War, the Rektor 100rd features a patented latching magazine box design to reduce reloading time.
An older model over-under shotgun. "They don't make 'em like they used to." has been crudely carved into the wooden backside of the stock.
An antique break-action, double-barrel shotgun that has been upgraded with an Ada kit and fashioned with scatter prisms.

The highly requested mix between gun and bow, that everyone wanted. It gives the user the option to set the trigger power on the fly, making the arc of the shots depend on the users needs. The further the draw string pulls the piston back before release the faster and longer the bullet will travel.
Manufactured and used by mobsters during the first gangsta era.
A very early magazine-based pistol. Made by the Haukland Company.
Semi-automatic foldable marksman rifle inspired by Japanese minimal housing. The manual claims that the barrel is not compatible with FM radio, even though it appears to be.
Very portable weapon. Seems to be specificly designed to make people quit smoking, once and for all.

The gentlemans automatic shotgun. A compact piece where the magazine doubles as a grip handle to compensate for the recoil. As the pellets travel such a miniscule distance in the barrel, this gun is especially good for those who need to hit many targets in a panic, or would prefer to aim a bit sporadically.
Designed and made in a sewing machine factory during the first robot war. Cocked easily by rotating the cylinder, which then shows the indicator in red. Known for its reliability.
A bullpup heavy assault rifle featuring a reciprocating recoil dampening system. Its metal housing makes it rather heavy to lug around.
You have a feeling that you've held this gun before...
A hand crafted sub machinegun with a body and foregrip made out of driftwood.
"And I looked, and behold a pale horse: and his name that sat on him was Death, and Hades was following close behind him."

A compact anti-materiel submachine gun designed for tank crews. This daring weapon of war was a last ditch attempt by Thomas Haukland to garner an upswing in profits, but that ultimately led to the company's bankruptcy.
An antique revolver heavily modified using several Ada kits. It can be fired in a semi auto fashion, or be slowly powered up to deal massive damage at the cost of more energy cells.
An assault rifle developed for amphibious operations. The Fisk is entirerly watertight except for its door-shaped ejection port.
Marketed as the obvious next step in the evolution of sawn-off shotguns. This newer model features an arm brace that helps prevent fractures.
"Leave only allies behind." - Saint Balthazar
This bird will make bullets fly.
A break-action laser sniper rifle, it super-charges energy cells to deliver devastating damage at the cost of a short delay when pulling the trigger. Iconic for its wide use in the Christmas War.
A light machinegun featuring double barrels, this gun that is essentially two guns packed into one has circulated heavily in recent border clashes on the 4th circle.
One of those modern sniper rifles that shoots very long. Has a retracting part of the barrel for recoil mitigation. Did I mention it was long?
The historical Haukland best seller. A Haukland customer once famously won "free Haukland Flash Hiders for life", and this largely contributed to the company's eventual bankruptcy.
A muzzle device designed to lower the recoil and spread of guns. Compatible with most barrels.
A muzzle device designed to lower the spread of guns. Compatible with most barrels.
A 2" multi-caliber, multi-threaded muzzle attachment designed to increase the length of a firearm barrel, thereby making any gun shoot more precisely.
A muzzle device designed to lower the sound signature of a firearm. Produced as a response to the Haukland Company discontinuing their production line of silencers.
A muzzle device designed to lower the recoil and spread of guns. Compatible with most barrels.
A muzzle device designed to lower the sound signature of a firearm. Made only in small amounts to be used by radio operators during the night raids of the first robot war.
A muzzle device designed to lower the recoil and spread of guns. Compatible with most barrels.
A 4" multi-caliber, multi-threaded muzzle attachment designed to increase the length of a firearm barrel, thereby making any gun shoot more precisely.
A makeshift muzzle device that can reduce spread and recoil somewhat. Fits most barrels.
A 6" multi-caliber, multi-threaded muzzle attachment designed to increase the length of a firearm barrel, thereby making any gun shoot more precisely.
A muzzle device designed to lower the recoil and spread of guns. Compatible with most barrels.
An improvised sound suppressor fashioned from a tin can.
A muzzle device designed to lower the sound signature of a firearm. Made by the Haukland Company.
An open red dot sight that aids in target acquisition. Compatible with most guns.
A compact collimator sight with an illuminated reticle for quicker target acquisition. Fits standard rails.
A long range rifle optic with an 12x zoom factor, designed for use by snipers.

A long range means of communication with a 
12x zoom factor, designed for use by snipers 
to deliver words of encouragement and love.
A firearm optic with an 4x zoom factor, designed to be effective both in close and long range engagements.
A firearm optic with an 8x zoom factor, designed for use by hunters.
A small optic with an 2x zoom factor, designed to be effective both in close to medium range engagements.
A tactical device with a built in laser module allowing for more accurate hip fire. Compatible with most guns. This one emits red light.
A tactical device with a built in laser module allowing for more accurate hip fire. Compatible with most guns. This one emits green light.
A tactical device with a built in laser module allowing for more accurate hip fire. Compatible with most guns. This one emits yellow light.
This mechanical device is constructed to provide extra force to the primer ignition of a firearm, increasing bullet velocity and reducing tumbling at the cost of forcing it to fire in semi automatic.
A mechanical device that can turn any semi automatic gun fully automatic.
When you lose a weapon this is attached to, it will drop out of the church collection box. One use only!
A toolkit containing everything needed to rebore a firearm barrel, changing the weapon's caliber to 12 gauge.
A toolkit containing everything needed to rebore a firearm barrel, changing the weapon's caliber to 7.62mm.
A toolkit containing everything needed to rebore a firearm barrel, changing the weapon's caliber to .50 BMG.
A toolkit containing everything needed to rebore a firearm barrel, changing the weapon's caliber to 5.56mm.
A toolkit containing everything needed to rebore a firearm barrel, changing the weapon's caliber to 9mm.
